      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BIRKIRKARA (4) made an encouraging return when he came from the back row to finish only 2.5m off the winner last week. Has won three of four second-up attempts so should be improved. Up to a distance where he owns a good record and is better served by this draw. REGAZZO DI TILLY (7) did a good job to overcome a 20m handicap and score at this circuit and distance when returning from Sydney last time out. Draws wide but he is capable. CALL TO ORDER (3) was far from disgraced when beaten only 3.4 from a back row draw last week and came from one spot wider than this to win here three back. The ace draw gives WHOS DELIGHT NZ (1) every chance to return to winning form while last-start placegetter CATSEYE BEACH (6) is worth including again.",
